hermes
------------------------------------------
Hermes is a graphics library designed to do a very limited number of
things and do them very well. It is also very easy to incorporate Hermes
into existing code. Hermes is intended for use either directly in an
application program or inside another graphics library.

The long feature list includes things like:

        * Palette handling
        * Clearing surfaces to a specific color
        * Conversion of images from one format to another

All features are implemented using an internal caching system,
drastically improving the performance of common operations such as table
lookups. In addition, on MMX systems, Hermes can use optimized MMX
assembler to further improve performance.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.21-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.21-1
  autoconf2.5-2.59-2
  automake1.9-1.9.6-1
  binutils-20050610-1
  cygport-0.2.4-1
  gawk-3.1.5-2
  gcc-core-3.4.4-1
  libtool1.5-1.5.22-1
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.clanlib.org/hermes/

Canonical download:
  http://www.clanlib.org/hermes/index.php?main=dls

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack hermes-1.3.3-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./hermes-1.3.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/hermes-1.3.3-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/hermes-1.3.3-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libHermes-devel-1.3.3-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libHermes1-1.3.3-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

